      "order": 1,
      "Description": "This lesson explores what happens when AI systems take control of network routing and optimisation, and why things do not always go to plan. You will learn how AI-driven decisions can introduce unexpected risks, from misrouted traffic to cascading failures across critical infrastructure. We will look at real-world scenarios where automation has both improved efficiency and caused significant disruption, helping you to understand the balance between reliability and risk. By the end of this lesson, you will have a clearer picture of how to evaluate AI tools in network environments and what safeguards are worth putting in place.",
